Duff and Phelps said it lowered itsratings on senior debt and preferred stock to DP-7 (low A) fromDP-6 (high A), affecting nearly 670 mln dlrs in debtsecurities.    The action reflects the increased financial leverageresulting from the company's 1986 acquisition of HammmermillPaper, which raised the fixed obligations ratio to 34 pct,compared with 26 pct in 1985, Duff and Phelps said. Reuter&#3;